examples.en: When air is warmed it expands and becomes lighter.
When water turns to steam, it expands.
The liquid expands and contracts with changes in temperature.
Her new book expands upon the theory propounded in her first book.
The longer version only expands, and in no way contradicts, the shorter one.
Light silk is best for parachutes, as it compresses well and then expands rapidly.
The river Clyde flows towards the north-west in a valley that gradually expands to a broad strath.
